data.name: Smoky Mushroom and Black Bean Enchiladas
data.quickTastyDescription: A rich, smoky, and satisfying dish featuring earthy mushrooms and hearty black beans wrapped in corn tortillas and topped with a zesty enchilada sauce.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add chopped onions and sauté until translucent.
Add minced garlic and sliced mushrooms to the skillet. Cook until mushrooms are browned and tender.
Stir in black beans, chipotle chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper. Cook for an additional 5 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld.
Spread 1/2 cup of enchilada sauce evenly on the bottom of a baking dish.
Spoon the mushroom and bean mixture into each tortilla, roll them up, and place seam-side down in the baking dish.
Pour the remaining enchilada sauce over the tortillas and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve with lime wedges.
data.detailedName: Smoky Mushroom and Black Bean Enchiladas with Cheddar Cheese and Fresh Cilantro
data.modifiersForBase: Stuffed with a smoky mushroom and black bean filling, topped with enchilada sauce and Cheddar cheese.
